MOSCOW, April 7. /TASS/. Co-chairs of the Russian-Turkish Public Forum (RTPF) Eleonora Mitrofanova and Ahmet Berat ·onkar discussed preparations for the next RTPF meeting and the preceding Forum of young leaders of Russia and Turkey that will be staged in Moscow from April 22 to 26, press service of the Russian Federal Agency for CIS Affairs (Rossotrudnichestvo) told TASS on Saturday.
“Co-chairs of the Russian-Turkish Public Forum (RTPF) discussed preparation for the fifth meeting of RTPF this summer in St. Petersburg, including suggested dates for the meeting, the itinerary of the forthcoming event, the composition of participants, and so on. Two events in the sphere of bilateral youth cooperation will be held in advance of the fifth RTPF meeting: the Forum of young leaders of Russia and Turkey to take place in Moscow from April 22 to 26 and the return visit of young Russian journalists to Turkey,” the agency said.
RTPF is operating within the framework of the High-Level Russian-Turkish Cooperation Council founded by presidents of both countries in 2010. The Council is called to coordinate implementation of political, trade-economic and cultural-humanitarian cooperation. Ten committees on various areas of interaction between the two countries are operating within the RTPF framework. The previous meeting of the Forum took place in Antalya, Turkey.
