MOSCOW, April 7. /TASS/. Russian judoka Khasan Khalmurzaev grabbed the bronze medal in the Men 81 kg category at the Grand Prix stage in Antalya, Turkey.
Luka Maisuradze from Georgia was first and Italy’s Christian Parlati was second.
The Russian athlete defeated Muhammed Koc from Turkey in the duel for the bronze medal.
